Mxp3 (
Figure 20
) with relatively narrow subtriangular ischium, ovoid merus, leaving long, wide rhomboidal hiatus between them; flagellum of exopod reaching just anterior to mesial margin of merus.

South Pacific: Vavao, Viti Islands ( Vava’u ?), Tonga [ type locality]; Lifu, Loyalty Islands; Vanuatu ; Lunga, Guadalcanal Island, Solomon Islands ( Hombron and Jacquinot 1842 – 1854 (1846); H. Milne Edwards 1853 ; present study). Erroneous records: Sydney ( Hess 1865 as
Sesarma schuetteii
); Madagascar (De Man 1887, table on p. 664).
